/*
 entry is the main starting point where webpack will begin bundling

 output is where the bundled output ultimately is placed

 loaders in webpack are tools that can look at different file types and process those files
 and give webpack the output to bundle into the single app.js file's output
 the above loader says if you see a .ts file, use the ts-loader to transpile into js before bundling into the app.js

 resolve tells webpack how to resolve modules
 What are the file extensions that webpack should be looking at
 */